Do not treat warnings as errors

There are additional warnings found with musl which are
treated as errors and fails the build, we have more combinations
than upstream supports to handle.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [oe specific]

From 4f12e7b5604a285b83f4af8afee56d4dd773ac3b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jameel Kareem <jkareem@murata.com>
Date: Wed, 4 Feb 2026 14:14:49 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] disable-dma-hciuart-kernel-crash

---
 drivers/tty/serial/imx.c | 10 ++++------
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/tty/serial/imx.c b/drivers/tty/serial/imx.c
index d5d24b00de00..2c31e47df358 100644
--- a/drivers/tty/serial/imx.c
+++ b/drivers/tty/serial/imx.c
@@ -1494,12 +1494,10 @@ static int imx_uart_startup(struct uart_port *port)
 
 	imx_uart_writel(sport, ucr4 & ~UCR4_DREN, UCR4);
 
-	/* Can we enable the DMA support? */
-	if (!uart_console(port) && imx_uart_dma_init(sport) == 0) {
-		lockdep_set_subclass(&port->lock, 1);
-		dma_is_inited = 1;
-	}
-
+/*  // Disable DMA support as the Kernel crashes when we make HCI_UART as module
+ 	if (!uart_console(port) && imx_uart_dma_init(sport) == 0)
+ 		dma_is_inited = 1;
+*/
 	uart_port_lock_irqsave(&sport->port, &flags);
 
 	/* Reset fifo's and state machines */
-- 
2.25.1

